Posted: Sun Jul 03, 2011 6:15 pm
things you will need at minimum;1 - 6/6.5 gallon bucket with lid with gromet2 - airlock (3 piece)3 - star san sanitiser4 - enough bottles for 5gallon batch5 - bottle caps6 - bottle capper7 - bucket with spigot for filling bottleseg: this from NB. http://www.northernbrewer.com/brewing/starter-kits/basic-starter-kit.htmland I'd throw in some star san too.then get yourself a recipe kit like this http://www.northernbrewer.com/brewing/the-innkeeper-limited-edition-extract-kit-1.html (Innkeeper is an awesome beer!)follow directions in recipe kit.give yourself a good half a day. say, start saturday morning as the first time will take you quite some time and be quite messy and take lots of cleaning up note, you will need to be able to boil about 3 gallons AT ROLLING BOIL (so a 4 gallon pot at minimum).this is easy with a propane burner and large pot. if you dont have a propane burner you can try it on your stove top but beware glasstops with the weight of 3+gallons (and the size of the pot), etc.in a pinch, find a turkey frier on special and season the shit outta the alu pot.walmart used to sell an 18qt (4.5gallon) enamel canning pot but I dont know if they do anymore.read this, how to brew 1st edition (free online).http://www.howtobrew.com/intro.html
