I started a batch on Wednesday with an ale extract kit from northern brewer and just tasted a hydrometer sample. It tastes like beer! Flat, but like beer! I was really worried when I screwed up mixing the batch because I was scared to pour in too much of the sludge at the bottom of my kettle. When the OG reading was pretty off (because I didn't dump enough wort and already filled it to 5 gallons...doh) I dumped some more of the settled wort in and got it at least closer to what the OG was supposed to be. It was supposed to be 1045 and I got it to 1040 at least (it was probably poorly mixed). Since this is supposed to be a beach beer I'm not overly concerned about it being too low. It does taste pretty weak right now though and I can barely notice any alcohol in it. Think that will be a problem?The reading I just took was 1.10 so I'm guessing its almost done fermenting? I'll leave it in the primary for at least another week to condition. The krausen (sp?) seemed to be retreating but since its in a bucket this was the first time I saw it. The airlock has definitely subsided its bubbling considerably.
