Posted: Sun Jul 10, 2011 7:55 pm
I'd leave it in the bucket until saturday then bottle it that morning. the less you take the lid off to take a reading the less chance of infection getting in. When you take your final reading make sure the bottling sugar is mixed in well first! boil some water, add in 2/3rd cup dextrose and nuke it in the microwave till its all dissolved, pour in bottling bucket, rack beer from primary into bottling bucket, swish it around to mix it, bottle! make sure you steralise your bottles, and put your caps into a bowl of starsan.
Dogmeat
