First beer brewed, fermented and bottled!Bottling is definitely the step I hate the most. Knocked my final gravity sample over and broke my hydrometer when I was starting to siphon (never got the reading), got a bit of trub in my bottling bucket because I was dumb with the autosiphon, accidentally stopped the siphon twice and had to restart it, probably introduced way too much oxygen in the way of bubbles because of that, and spilled too much beer when bottling requiring me to rinse and dry them once they were done.My reward is 43 12-ounce and 4 grolsch bottles of (hopefully) delicious beer! The sample I tried was pretty tasty.
