Posted: Sat Aug 20, 2011 2:23 pm
When sparring all grain, the amount of sparge water is going to be limited by your boil kettle and/or the amount of time you wish to spend boiling the collected wort down to terminal volume. Since your recipe indicates that you're expected to collect more than 5 gallons, you will just end up short on your initial gravity.
