Had a holiday today, so got my Columbus Day brew on. This a new creation for me, a Pumpkin ale based around a Rochefort 8 clone. I roasted and mashed four pie pumpkins, filtered and added to the boil water for the Rochefort clone, and then added 2 tsps of a pie spice mix (equal parts cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, and cloves) and 1 tbsp of vanilla bean extract. Fermenting it with London Ale III from Wyeast. I liked the flocculation and attenuation profile for the desired end result, a bit sweet and spicy. Gravity is around 1.086. Once I transfer to secondary I'll check the spice and vanilla flavors and add more if needed.
